<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="185" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,612,1106]" pageId="9" pageNumber="185">
<emphasis box="[199,315,721,745]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="185" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,721,745]" pageId="9" pageNumber="185">Remarks</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rahayu &amp; Forest, 2009:" authorityYear="1317" box="[323,547,722,745]" class="Malacostraca" family="Diogenidae" genus="Paguristes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="185" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrops">
<emphasis box="[323,547,722,745]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="185">Paguristes macrops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by having rounded red spot on each of the mesial and lateral faces of the meri of the chelipeds and second and third pereopods. This character is also seen in 
<taxonomicName authority="(H. Milne Edwards, 1836)" baseAuthorityName="H. Milne Edwards" baseAuthorityYear="1836" class="Malacostraca" family="Diogenidae" genus="Paguristes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="185" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gonagrus">
<emphasis box="[1256,1391,758,781]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="185">P. gonagrus</emphasis>
(H. 
<bibRefCitation author="Milne Edwards, H." box="[151,400,793,817]" pageId="9" pageNumber="185" pagination="257 - 288" refId="ref13840" refString="Milne Edwards, H. (1836) Observations zoologiques sur les Pagures et description d'un nouveau genre de la tribu des Paguriens. Annales des Sciences Naturelle Zoologie, Paris, ser. 2, 6, 257 - 288." type="journal article" year="1836">Milne Edwards, 1836</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Alcock, 1905" authorityName="Alcock" authorityYear="1905" box="[421,863,793,817]" class="Malacostraca" family="Diogenidae" genus="Paguristes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="185" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balanophylus">
<emphasis box="[421,699,793,817]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="185">Paguristes balanophylus</emphasis>
Alcock, 1905
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="McLaughlin &amp; Rahayu, 2005" authorityName="McLaughlin &amp; Rahayu" authorityYear="2005" box="[876,1432,793,817]" class="Malacostraca" family="Diogenidae" genus="Paguristes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="185" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alcocki">
<emphasis box="[876,1086,793,817]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="185">Paguristes alcocki</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="McLaughlin, P. A. &amp; Rahayu, D. L." box="[1094,1432,793,817]" pageId="9" pageNumber="185" pagination="37 - 62" refId="ref13743" refString="McLaughlin, P. A. &amp; Rahayu, D. L. (2005) Two new species of Paguristes (Decapoda: Anomura: Paguroidea: Diogenidae) and a review of Paguristes pusillus Henderson. Zootaxa, 1083: 37 - 62." type="journal article" year="2005">McLaughlin &amp; Rahayu, 2005</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="McLaughlin &amp; Rahayu, 2005" authorityName="McLaughlin &amp; Rahayu" authorityYear="2005" box="[151,750,829,853]" class="Malacostraca" family="Diogenidae" genus="Paguristes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="185" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lewinsohni">
<emphasis box="[151,401,829,853]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="185">Paguristes lewinsohni</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="McLaughlin, P. A. &amp; Rahayu, D. L." box="[410,750,829,853]" pageId="9" pageNumber="185" pagination="37 - 62" refId="ref13743" refString="McLaughlin, P. A. &amp; Rahayu, D. L. (2005) Two new species of Paguristes (Decapoda: Anomura: Paguroidea: Diogenidae) and a review of Paguristes pusillus Henderson. Zootaxa, 1083: 37 - 62." type="journal article" year="2005">McLaughlin &amp; Rahayu, 2005</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Rahayu &amp; Forest, 2009" authorityName="Rahayu &amp; Forest" authorityYear="2009" box="[763,1253,829,853]" class="Malacostraca" family="Diogenidae" genus="Paguristes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="185" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aulacis">
<emphasis box="[763,973,829,853]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="185">Paguristes aulacis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Rahayu, D. L. &amp; Forest, J" box="[982,1253,829,853]" pageId="9" pageNumber="185" pagination="1307 - 1338" refId="ref15237" refString="Rahayu, D. L. &amp; Forest, J (2009) Le genre Paguristes Dana aux Philippines avec la description de deux nouvelles especes (Decapoda, Anomura, Diogenidae). Crustaceana, 82 (10), 1307 - 1338." type="journal article" year="2009">Rahayu &amp; Forest, 2009</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="185">
<taxonomicName box="[1316,1436,830,853]" class="Malacostraca" family="Diogenidae" genus="Paguristes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="185" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Paguristes</taxonomicName>
ocellus
</emphasis>
Komai, 2010, but there are morphological and other colour differences among these species. The specimens in the present study agree well with the original description and the colouration of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rahayu &amp; Forest, 2009:" authorityYear="1317" box="[1088,1310,902,925]" class="Malacostraca" family="Diogenidae" genus="Paguristes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="185" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrops">
<emphasis box="[1088,1310,902,925]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="185">Paguristes macrops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but minor differences are noted: the ocular peduncles that are shorter than the shield, and the mesial face of the dactyl of each cheliped has only one longitudinal row of tubercles. The specimens collected (2.54, 
<quantity box="[1103,1202,973,997]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.45" pageId="9" pageNumber="185" unit="mm" value="3.45">3.45 mm</quantity>
in shield length) are smaller than the specimens examined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Rahayu, D. L. &amp; Forest, J" box="[615,883,1009,1033]" pageId="9" pageNumber="185" pagination="1307 - 1338" refId="ref15237" refString="Rahayu, D. L. &amp; Forest, J (2009) Le genre Paguristes Dana aux Philippines avec la description de deux nouvelles especes (Decapoda, Anomura, Diogenidae). Crustaceana, 82 (10), 1307 - 1338." type="journal article" year="2009">Rahayu &amp; Forest (2009</bibRefCitation>
, 3.0– 
<quantity box="[946,1030,1009,1033]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.1" pageId="9" pageNumber="185" unit="mm" value="9.1">9.1 mm</quantity>
in shield length), and too limited to evaluate whether these differences are only intraspecific variations or they warrant the separation of species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
